# Signal Format

Every signal must follow this structure exactly.

## Dashboard Card (Compact View)

```
TSLA
Bullish ↑
Confidence: 72%
Expected Move: +3% to +7%
Horizon: 5 days

Key Drivers:
- Strong earnings sentiment
- High social momentum
- Positive sector trend

Risk: Medium
Rank: #5
```

## Expanded View

### Prediction
- Signal: Bullish | Bearish | Crash Risk
- Confidence: 0–100%
- Expected Move: low% to high%
- Horizon: N days
- Crash Risk: %

### Why This Call
- 2–4 bullet points: human-readable reasons

### Evidence
- Number of supporting articles
- Source credibility rating
- Official filings referenced (if any)

### Historical Analog
- Avg move in similar past scenarios
- Hit rate (%)

### Risk Flags
- Any warning factors (e.g., overextended rally, sector volatility)

---

## Scoring Formula

```
Score =
  (Sentiment × Credibility)
+ (Event Severity × Novelty)
+ (Historical Reaction Weight)
+ (Social Momentum)   ← optional MVP+
```

Outputs two scores:
- **Opportunity Score** — 0.0 to 1.0 (upside potential)
- **Crash Risk Score** — 0.0 to 1.0 (downside risk)

## Signal Direction Rules
| Opportunity Score | Crash Risk Score | Direction     |
|-------------------|-----------------|---------------|
| > 0.6             | < 0.3           | Bullish       |
| < 0.4             | > 0.6           | Bearish       |
| any               | > 0.75          | Crash Risk    |
| 0.4–0.6           | 0.3–0.6         | Neutral       |

## Confidence → Expected Move Mapping
- Confidence 80%+: tight range, high conviction
- Confidence 60–79%: moderate range
- Confidence <60%: wide range, low conviction

## Ranking
- Rank by opportunity score (descending)
- Crash Risk signals appear in a separate section
- Top 10 shown on dashboard by default
